## CS Concepts

An **event** is an action that causes something to happen. For example, web pages may include a drop down menu when you roll over the navigation bar with your mouse.  The "mouse rollover" is an action that causes the menu to drop down.

### Student Video

Watch the video, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u0WV9shCoak" target="blank"> "The Big Event Jr.,"</a>, that first introduces "events" to students in Course A - Lesson 11:  The Big Event Jr. 

## Learning Platform Features

Students use Play Lab to program "events" in animated games they create. 

Watch the video, <a href="https://youtu.be/nVsZyQIZyPc" target="blank">"Introduction to Play Lab (Pre-reader version),"</a> that introduces Play Lab to students.

